Class GraphSpaceClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.graphspace.javaclient.GraphSpaceClient

  • public class GraphSpaceClient
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the main class that exposes all the graph, layout and group methods to the user. Users can explore each of the methods in the respective classes.

      • GraphSpaceClient

        public GraphSpaceClient(java.lang.String host,
                        java.lang.String username,
                        java.lang.String password)
        Create client object with host, username and password
        Parameters:
        host(String) - host where graphs are located (default: http://www.graphspace.org)
        username(String) - email of the user to be connected
        password(String) - password of the user to be connected

      • GraphSpaceClient

        public GraphSpaceClient(java.lang.String username,
                        java.lang.String password)
        Create client object with username and password. The user can set the default host in Config.java. By default, Config.HOST = http://graphspace.org
        Parameters:
        username(String) - email of the user to be connected
        password(String) - password of the user to be connected
